The image presents a graph with the x-axis labeled "Digital input code" and the y-axis labeled "Differential linearity error". The graph displays the relationship between the digital input code (DAC) and the differential linearity error, represented by a purple line on the graph.

The graph shows that as the DAC increases, the differential linearity error also increases. This suggests that there is a negative correlation between the two variables.
